			<td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span> 
			4/25 6:53am 
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: hub/routers?			
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Well, it all depends on what you want.  If you just want internet access for multiple machines, a hub is fine.  Usually you will need to have your ISP provide multiple IPs (static or dynamic, depending on availability/price)  Not much by way of security with a hub, but firewall software is easy to come by. <br>  <br> Personally, I prefer routers.  Most routers have build in (hardware) firewall capabilities.    You only need one IP addy.  Most routers are as low as 70 dollars. <br>  <br> Anywho, my preference is either <br> linksys or netgear, but for the most part, you learn which vendors to trust by experience.  If you are purchasing one from a store, seriously look into their return/exchange policy. <br>  <br> Online, go here: <br>  <br> http://www.pricewatch.com/ <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> blah blah blah, enough typing <br>  <br> 
